##There's been a major discovery in Zhong Nanshan, neglect or missed cases

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

Zhong Nanshan's team recently published an Original article in the The New England Journal of Medicine, the most influential Journal of General Medicine. The data source of this paper is under the support and coordination of the National Health Commission, from December 11,2019 to January 29,2020, a total of 1,099 cases of laboratory confirmed COVID-19 infection (hereinafter referred to as NCP infection) were collected from 552 hospitals in 30 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities in China, led by Academician Zhong Nanshan.

Screenshot of a research paper published in the Journal The New England Journal of Medicine

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On May 5, Academician Zhong Nanshan made an exclusive interpretation of the main highlights and clinical significance of the paper, providing new ideas for clinical treatment.

What are the key findings and clinical implications of the study?

1) this study collected the clinical information of a large sample of patients (over 1000 cases) for the first time in China. Many patients were treated outside Hubei Province, most of them were non-severe cases (84.3%) , and 15.7% were severe cases

2) the case fatality rate calculated in this study (1.4%) is closer to that reported by the National Health Commission (about 2.3%) 

3) only 1.9% of the patients had a history of direct contact with wild animals, 31.3% of the residents living outside Wuhan had been to Wuhan in the past 2 weeks, and 72.3% of the patients had contact with people in Wuhan in the past 2 Weeks;

4) it was pointed out that 56.2% of the patients with NCP had no fever at the time of admission, but 88.7% of the patients had fever as the disease progressed

5) pointing out that gastrointestinal symptoms (including nausea, vomiting and diarrhea) are relatively rare, pointing out evidence of new coronavirus transmission through the digestive tract (virus was isolated from feces, damaged Mucosa of the gastrointestinal tract and hemorrhage) , and suggesting the need to pay attention to the prevention of new coronavirus transmission caused by sewage pollution;

6) it was pointed out that there were some patients with new crown infection who had positive nucleic acid test and had clinical symptoms but did not show any abnormal imaging at the time of admission, and the proportion of non-severe patients (17.9%) was much higher than that of severe patients (2.9%) ;

7) noting that the lymphocyte reduction was seen in 83.2% of patients with NCP, the search for the key mechanism of viral lymphocyte should inspire clinicians to improve the success rate of treatment by regulating the patient's immune function.

How does the foreign colleague evaluate the paper?

The New England Journal of Medicine highlights the new crown disease, and professors Anthony Fauci, Clifford Lane, and Robert Redfield of the NIH wrote an article titled Covid-19 Foshan navigating the uncharted, the findings of this study suggest that new crown outbreaks may ultimately be more similar to seasonal influenza (case fatality rate close to 0.1%) or influenza pandemics (similar to the 1957 and 1968 pandemics) , in contrast, SARS and Mers have high case fatality rates (9% to 10% and 36% , respectively) .
